18/02/2007
STRASBOURG, France -- The Council of Europe Congress of Local and Regional Authorities' Bureau issued a statement Friday (February 16th), voicing concern over tension in Kosovo lately. It urged all parties to show restraint and a constructive approach in the UN-mediated future status negotiations. The statement also reaffirmed the Congress' readiness to provide assistance and announced that later this year, it would begin work on a new report on Kosovo's local self-government situation. (CoE web site, Tanjug - 16/02/07)
